.zshrc

Robby Russel's wonderful oh-my-zsh
(https://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh).

I also got some ideas for my cutom zsh prompt from Steve Losh
(http://stevelosh.com/blog/2010/02/my-extravagant-zsh-prompt/).


.vimrc

My vimrc file started life as a direct copy of Amir
Salihefendic's, (http://amix.dk/vim/vimrc.html). I also stole
some ideas from the answers to this stackoverflow question:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/164847/what-is-in-your-vimrc


.tmux.conf

I based my .tmux.conf on Tony Narloc's
(https://github.com/tony/tmux-config). I also got
some tips on tmux and mouse interactions from Dan Lowe
(http://tangledhelix.com/blog/2012/07/16/tmux-and-mouse-mode/). The
settings for using Ctrl-z (instead of Ctrl-b) come from
https://gist.github.com/2591700


.ssh/rc

The tmux/ssh agent fix came from
http://superuser.com/questions/180148/how-do-you-get-screen-to-automatically-connect-to-the-current-ssh-agent-when-re

